As an AP interested in listing my assistive products or services on the Y4J platform,
I want to click a registration link from the Y4J Hub portal and complete my onboarding form,
so that my organization can be verified and added to the PwD catalog.
 
Acceptance Criteria
1.	Access and Navigation for RegistFration
o	A visible “Register as Assistive Partner” link is available on the Y4J Hub portal.
o	Clicking the link redirects the user to the AP Registration page of the PwD Catalog portal
o	The page clearly mentions the purpose of registration and eligibility criteria for APs.
2.	Sign in-
o	A visible “Sign in with Swarajability” link is available on the Y4J Hub portal, for already registered APs or the one who are there on Swarajability platform.
o	It will be a SSO login, single click will navigate APs to the Assistive Partner Portal’s dashboard.
3.	Registration Form
o	The registration form includes the following mandatory fields:
	Organization Name
	Type of Organization (Manufacturer / Distributor / NGO / Service Provider)
	Contact Person Name
	Official Email ID
	Phone Number
	Registered Address
	Short Description of Offerings (devices, services, or products)
o	Optional fields include:
	Website / Social Media Links
	Upload Organization Logo or Certificate
4.	Form Behavior & Validation
o	The form validates all required fields before submission.
o	Error messages are displayed for missing or invalid inputs.
o	The form cannot be submitted until all required data is entered correctly.
5.	Submission Confirmation
o	Upon successful submission, a confirmation message is displayed on screen (e.g., “Thank you for registering. The Y4J team will review your details and contact you shortly.”).
o	An acknowledgment email is automatically sent to the registered email address summarizing the submitted information.
6.	Admin Notification
o	A notification email containing AP registration details is sent to the Y4J admin for verification.
o	The AP’s registration record appears in the admin dashboard with status “Pending Review.”
7.	Duplicate Registration Handling
o	If a AP attempts to register using an email already in the system, a message appears: “This email is already registered. Please log in or contact Y4J support.”
8.	Accessibility & UI Standards
o	The registration page follows WCAG 2.1 AA accessibility standards.
o	All form fields have proper labels, clear error prompts, and high-contrast text.
o	The page supports screen readers and keyboard navigation.
9.	Post-Submission Workflow 
o	The admin reviews and approves or rejects the registration request. 
o	Upon approval, the vendor receives an activation email with login details or next steps to list products/services. 
o	Upon rejection, the vendor is notified with reason or guidance to reapply.

